Sentencas: This study explores the potentiality of the zinc andiron-basedperovskite cathode materials in intermediate temperature solid oxidefuel cells (SOFCs), for which BaFe0.8Zn0.1Nb0.1O3-delta (BFZNO:1) and BaFe0.6Zn0.3Nb0.1O3-delta (BFZNO:2)materials with cubic crystal phase purity were considered.
Titulo: Characterization of BaFe0.8Zn0.1Nb0.1O3-δ and BaFe0.6Zn0.3Nb0.1O3-δ Perovskite Cathode Materials for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: These materialshave been effectively synthesized by employing the sol-gelautocombustion process.
Titulo: Characterization of BaFe0.8Zn0.1Nb0.1O3-δ and BaFe0.6Zn0.3Nb0.1O3-δ Perovskite Cathode Materials for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The structural details and phase purity ofthe synthesized nanomaterials were confirmed from the data obtainedfrom the XRD patterns, while SEM images revealed that both materialsare highly porous with grain sizes of 200-250 nm and 55-65nm for BFZNO:1 and BFZNO:2, respectively.
Titulo: Characterization of BaFe0.8Zn0.1Nb0.1O3-δ and BaFe0.6Zn0.3Nb0.1O3-δ Perovskite Cathode Materials for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The DC electrical conductivityof BFZNO:1 was estimated as 3.98 S/cm and that of BFZNO:2 as 3.56S/cm at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Characterization of BaFe0.8Zn0.1Nb0.1O3-δ and BaFe0.6Zn0.3Nb0.1O3-δ Perovskite Cathode Materials for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The BFZNO:1 exhibited a superior current densityof 1360 mAcm(-2), a power density of 530 mW cm(-2), and an open circuit voltage of 1.29 at an intermediatetemperature of 700 degrees C, confirming the potential of Zn and Fe-basedperovskite cathode materials for application in intermediate temperatureSOFCs.
Titulo: Characterization of BaFe0.8Zn0.1Nb0.1O3-δ and BaFe0.6Zn0.3Nb0.1O3-δ Perovskite Cathode Materials for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
